<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="1208" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[813,1420,427,1175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,974,607,631]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208">Identification.</emphasis>
Eyes prominent (more than nine omma- tidia along the shortest axis); frontal lobes in full-face view subquadrate; anterior margin of clypeus in fullface view concave, lacking shiny cuticular strip; neck lacking median carina; mandibles elongate; anterior margin of pronotum in dorsal view convex, with median emargination and no lateral thickening; and mesopleu- ral ventral carina in lateral view well-developed, thick (
<bibRefCitation author="Lattke JE" box="[820,954,876,900]" firstAuthor="Lattke" journalOrPublisher="Arquivos de Zoologia" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208" pagination="121 - 221" part="34" refId="ref16899" refString="Lattke JE (1997) Revision del genero Apterostigma Mayr: (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Arquivos de Zoologia 34 (5): 121 - 221. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2176 - 7793. v 34 i 5 p 121 - 221" title="Revision del genero Apterostigma Mayr: (Hymenoptera: Formicidae)" type="journal article" year="1997">Lattke 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="1208" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[813,1420,427,1175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,961,915,939]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208">Distribution.</emphasis>
In Colombia, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1938" box="[1140,1300,915,939]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Apterostigma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianum">
<emphasis box="[1140,1300,915,939]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208">A. bolivianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was only known from Amazonas, thus the new record from Antioquia (
<figureCitation box="[873,950,982,1007]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[168,232,1781,1801]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,164,1723]" captionTargetId="figure-96@2.[168,1419,160,1736]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. Geographic distribution of non-leaf-cutting fungus-growing ant species in Colombia. A. Apterostigma pilosum species-group. B. Genus Cyphomyrmex. C. Apterostigma auriculatum species-group, and genera Mycocepurus, Myrmicocrypta, and Mycetomoellerius. D. Genera Sericomyrmex and Paratrachymyrmex." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4069326" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4069326/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
) suggests this species might be broadly dis- tributed throughout the country (
<figureCitation box="[1175,1256,1016,1040]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[168,232,1781,1801]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,164,1723]" captionTargetId="figure-96@2.[168,1419,160,1736]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. Geographic distribution of non-leaf-cutting fungus-growing ant species in Colombia. A. Apterostigma pilosum species-group. B. Genus Cyphomyrmex. C. Apterostigma auriculatum species-group, and genera Mycocepurus, Myrmicocrypta, and Mycetomoellerius. D. Genera Sericomyrmex and Paratrachymyrmex." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4069326" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4069326/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Weber NA" box="[1280,1415,1016,1040]" firstAuthor="Weber" journalOrPublisher="Revista de Entomologia" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208" pagination="154 - 206" part="9" refId="ref18989" refString="Weber NA (1938) The biology of the fungus-growing ants. Part IV. Additional new forms. Part V. The Attini of Bolivia. Revista de Entomologia 9 (1 - 2): 154 - 206." title="The biology of the fungus-growing ants. Part IV. Additional new forms. Part V. The Attini of Bolivia" type="journal article" year="1938">Weber 1938</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kempf WW" box="[813,951,1050,1074]" firstAuthor="Kempf" journalOrPublisher="Studia Entomologica" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208" pagination="1 - 344" part="15" refId="ref16872" refString="Kempf WW (1972) Catalogo abreviado das formigas da regiao neotro- pical (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Studia Entomologica 15: 1 - 344." title="Catalogo abreviado das formigas da regiao neotro- pical (Hymenoptera: Formicidae)" type="journal article" year="1972">Kempf 1972</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fernandez F &amp; Baena ML &amp; Palacio EE" box="[965,1209,1050,1074]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Fernandez" journalOrPublisher="Tacaya" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208" pagination="9 - 10" part="5" refId="ref16182" refString="Fernandez F, Baena ML, Palacio EE (1996) Hormigas de Colombia V: el genero Stenamma Westwood. Tacaya 5: 9 - 10." title="Hormigas de Colombia V: el genero Stenamma Westwood" type="journal article" year="1996">Fernández et al. 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lattke JE" box="[1223,1358,1050,1074]" firstAuthor="Lattke" journalOrPublisher="Arquivos de Zoologia" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208" pagination="121 - 221" part="34" refId="ref16899" refString="Lattke JE (1997) Revision del genero Apterostigma Mayr: (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Arquivos de Zoologia 34 (5): 121 - 221. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2176 - 7793. v 34 i 5 p 121 - 221" title="Revision del genero Apterostigma Mayr: (Hymenoptera: Formicidae)" type="journal article" year="1997">Lattke 1997</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Apterostigma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1208">Apterostigma bolivianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also known from the following countries in northwestern South America: Bolivia, Ec- uador, Peru, and Venezuela.
</paragraph>
